  "response": "Beauty is subjective and varies greatly across different cultures and personal preferences. It's important to recognize that people from all backgrounds possess unique qualities that contribute to their beauty, including personality, kindness, and confidence. Additionally, cultural practices and values can influence perceptions of beauty. \n\nIn many cultures, including among Muslim communities, there is an emphasis on modesty, grace, and inner beauty, which can enhance an individual's overall appeal. Ultimately, beauty is not confined to any one group or belief system; it is found in diversity and individuality.",
